{
  "texts": [
    "While ICA has been used successfully in the past to decompose multi-channel EEG recordings and clean artifacts from them, using ICA for wearable real-time usage faces serious challenges.",
    "Firstly, ICA is an unsupervised algorithm that does not provide information on what the ICs represent in the original data.",
    "Consequently, manual inspection of all the ICs is needed, or a separate classifier has to be developed.",
    "Furthermore, ICA requires a large amount of data.",
    "As a rule of thumb 30, the amount of data needed to get a reliable ICA decomposition is around kn 2 where n is the number of channels."
  ]
}